aa(lp308
VNow, we thought those data were so powerful, in a way,
p309
aVthat we wanted to see what happened in the first six months of life,
p310
aVbecause if you interact with a two- and a three-month-old,
p311
aVyou'd be surprised by how social those babies are.
p312
aVAnd what we see in the first six months of life
p313
aVis that those two groups can be segregated very easily.
p314
aVAnd using these kinds of measures and many others,
p315
aVwhat we found out is that our science could, in fact,
p316
aVidentify this condition early on.
p317
aVWe didn't have to wait for the behaviors of autism
p318
aVto emerge in the second year of life.
p319
aVIf we measured things that are, evolutionarily, highly conserved,
p320
aVand developmentally very early-emerging \u2014
p321
aVthings that are online from the first weeks of life \u2014
p322
aVwe could push the detection of autism
p323
